==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resumption
<hw>Re*sump"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧sumption</ets>, L. <ets>resumptio</ets> restoration,
recovery, fr. <ets>resumere</ets>. See <er>Resume</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of resuming; <as>as, the <ex>resumption</ex> of
a grant, of delegated powers, of an argument, of specie payments,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eng.Law)</fld> <def>The taking again into the
king's hands of such lands or tenements as he had granted to any man on
false suggestions or other error.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resumptive</ent>⟦br⟧
